State: `mode` (line 596, initialised from localStorage `agentx_mode`).

#### c) Play / Stop (Send / Stop) Buttons

**Lines 1294-1322** in the JSX:

```jsx
<div className="input-actions">
  <button
    className="stop-btn"
    disabled={!streaming}
    onClick={() => {
      abortRef.current?.abort();
      setMessages((prev) => { /* ... mark last message as stopped */ });
    }}
  >
    &#9632;               {/* Unicode black square — the Stop icon */}
  </button>
  <button
    className="send-btn"
    onClick={sendMessage}
    disabled={streaming || !input.trim()}
  >
    &#9654;               {/* Unicode right-pointing triangle — the Play/Send icon */}
  </button>
</div>
```

- **Stop** button is enabled only when `streaming === true`. It calls `abortRef.current?.abort()`.
- **Send/Play** button is enabled only when `!streaming && input.trim() !== ""`. It calls `sendMessage()`.

Streaming state: `streaming` (line 554), set to `true` when a message is being sent from the API (line 1012).

