### 3. Activity Window and Its Resize Functionality

#### a) Activity Window Definition

The activity panel is rendered at **lines 1326-1337** of `App.jsx`:

```jsx
{sidebarVisible && (
  <div className="activity-panel-wrap" style={{ width: activityWidth }}>
    <ActivityPanel
      activities={activities}
      streaming={streaming}
      subagents={subagents}
      activeSession={activeSubagentId}
      onSelectSubagent={selectSubagent}
      hideToolDetails={hideToolDetails}
    />
  </div>
)}
```

The `ActivityPanel` component itself lives in **`/home/glompy/Desktop/ASTROCYTECH/Agent_X/ui/src/components/ActivityPanel.jsx`**.

It is conditionally rendered based on `sidebarVisible` (a boolean derived from `sidebarPref`, line 601: `const sidebarVisible = sidebarPref === "auto"`).

#### b) Resize Handle (Dragging Left Edge Left/Right)

The resize handle is a `<div>` rendered at **line 1325** of `App.jsx`:

```jsx
<div
  className={`resize-handle${dragging ? " active" : ""}`}
  onMouseDown={onHandleMouseDown}
/>
```

It sits between the chat area and the activity panel in the flex layout (the `.main-content` row: `.chat-area`  |  `.resize-handle`  |  `.activity-panel-wrap`).

#### c) Resize State Variables

**Lines 578-586** of `App.jsx`:

```jsx
const [activityWidth, setActivityWidth] = useState(() => {
  try {
    const saved = localStorage.getItem("agentx_activity_width");
    return saved ? parseInt(saved, 10) : 420;
  } catch { return 420; }
});
const [dragging, setDragging] = useState(false);
const dragStartX = useRef(0);
const dragStartWidth = useRef(0);
```

- `activityWidth`: current width of the activity panel (default 420px, persisted in localStorage under `agentx_activity_width`).
- `dragging`: tracks whether the user is currently dragging the resize handle.
- `dragStartX` / `dragStartWidth`: refs to capture the mouse X and panel width at the start of the drag.

#### d) Mouse Down Handler (Start Drag)

**Lines 607-612**:

```jsx
const onHandleMouseDown = useCallback((e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  setDragging(true);
  dragStartX.current = e.clientX;
  dragStartWidth.current = activityWidth;
}, [activityWidth]);
```

#### e) Mouse Move / Mouse Up Handlers (Drag Logic)

**Lines 614-637** — a `useEffect` that sets up global listeners only when `dragging === true`:

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  if (!dragging) return;
  document.body.style.userSelect = "none";
  const onMove = (e) => {
    const newWidth = dragStartWidth.current - (e.clientX - dragStartX.current);
    const clamped = Math.max(280, Math.min(800, newWidth));
    setActivityWidth(clamped);
  };
  const onUp = () => {
    setDragging(false);
    document.body.style.userSelect = "";
    setActivityWidth((w) => {
      try { localStorage.setItem("agentx_activity_width", String(w)); } catch {}
      return w;
    });
  };
  document.addEventListener("mousemove", onMove);
  document.addEventListener("mouseup", onUp);
  return () => {
    document.removeEventListener("mousemove", onMove);
    document.removeEventListener("mouseup", onUp);
    document.body.style.userSelect = "";
  };
}, [dragging]);
```

**Key mechanics of the resize:**
- `newWidth = dragStartWidth.current - (e.clientX - dragStartX.current)`  
  Dragging **left** (decreasing `clientX`) **increases** the activity panel width; dragging **right** decreases it.
- Width is **clamped** between **280px** and **800px**.
- On mouse up, the final width is saved to `localStorage` under `agentx_activity_width`.

#### f) CSS for the Resize Handle

From **`App.css`**, lines 672-695:

```css
.resize-handle {
  width: 12px;
  cursor: col-resize;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  background: transparent;
  position: relative;
  z-index: 10;
  background-clip: content-box;
  padding: 0 4px;
}
.resize-handle::after {
  content: "";
  display: block;
  height: 100%;
  width: 4px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  border-radius: 2px;
  background: transparent;
  transition: background 0.15s;
}
.resize-handle:hover::after,
.resize-handle.active::after {
  background: #4a6fa5;
}
```

The handle itself is 12px wide (with 4px padding on each side), with a 4px wide visual bar centered inside it. It turns blue on hover/active.

